      <akn:section eId="sec_50_1301_53">
        <akn:num>50-1301.53</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Alternate methods of giving proof.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_50-1301_53_1">
      <akn:num>(1)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A certificate of insurance, as provided in § 50-1301.54 or 50-1301.55; or</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_50-1301_53_2">
      <akn:num>(2)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A certificate of self-insurance, as provided in § 50-1301.79,  supplemented by an agreement by the self-insurer that, with respect to accidents occurring while the certificate is in force, he will pay the same amounts that an insurer would have been obliged to pay under an owner’s motor vehicle liability policy if it had issued such a policy to said self-insurer.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
